1
00:00:03,003 --> 00:00:05,806
When Machi Sangenya, a genius realtor,

2
00:00:06,273 --> 00:00:09,777
caught a glimpse of happiness as a woman,

3
00:00:10,244 --> 00:00:15,249
it was also the same moment
when a dark flame lit

4
00:00:15,549 --> 00:00:18,919
in the chivalrous heart of Kenji Rusudo.

5
00:00:24,258 --> 00:00:25,726
WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON

6
00:00:25,793 --> 00:00:27,962
It's nice to shop during the week.

7
00:00:28,429 --> 00:00:30,264
Today is Wednesday, so it's our day off.

8
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:33,601
What do you do?

9
00:00:35,002 --> 00:00:36,570
I'm a realtor.

10
00:00:38,572 --> 00:00:39,874
I'm ready.

11
00:00:41,575 --> 00:00:42,676
I'm opening it.

12
00:00:48,382 --> 00:00:49,250
What do you think?

13
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:51,585
You look wonderful.

14
00:00:53,220 --> 00:00:56,323
Sir, you are more handsome
than Tom Cruise.

15
00:00:56,624 --> 00:00:58,893
Please say Brad Pitt instead.

16
00:00:59,226 --> 00:01:00,327
My mistake.

17
00:01:01,328 --> 00:01:02,930
You two are both exaggerating.

18
00:01:03,798 --> 00:01:07,268
If I wear this to work,
everyone will be shocked.

19
00:01:07,535 --> 00:01:12,239
When your impression changes,
so will the sales department.

20
00:01:12,306 --> 00:01:15,810
People need that kind of stimulation
once in a while.

21
00:01:16,210 --> 00:01:18,979
So if I wear this,
it will have a surprising effect

22
00:01:19,046 --> 00:01:20,448
and more houses will sell?

23
00:01:20,648 --> 00:01:24,618
Yes, you wear
fashionable clothes to sell houses.

24
00:01:25,486 --> 00:01:27,188
It's to sell houses…

25
00:01:28,255 --> 00:01:29,523
Then, let's buy it.

26
00:01:30,057 --> 00:01:30,925
Let's buy it!

27
00:01:31,358 --> 00:01:32,860
-To sell houses!
-To sell houses!

28
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:36,864
Oh, time flies.

29
00:01:37,998 --> 00:01:40,067
Niwano, get some beer.

30
00:01:40,401 --> 00:01:43,904
What? Is that okay?

31
00:01:44,405 --> 00:01:48,676
Well, we are working on our day off.
It's fine to have some beer.

32
00:01:49,076 --> 00:01:51,679
Oh, this is exciting.

33
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:54,148
A beer! A beer!

34
00:01:54,415 --> 00:01:56,150
-Here you go!
-Thank you.

35
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,752
Let's drink!

36
00:02:01,922 --> 00:02:07,695
Niwano, you have a habit of elongating
certain words when you speak.

37
00:02:07,761 --> 00:02:09,663
It sounds like Mika Shirasu, so stop it.

38
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:12,700
I'll be careful.
Oh, I'm like Mika Shirasu?

39
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:16,937
Now, for us singles
who are devoted to work,

40
00:02:17,438 --> 00:02:18,973
-cheers!
-Cheers!

41
00:02:23,043 --> 00:02:24,545
It's delicious!

42
00:02:24,912 --> 00:02:26,647
Oh, I did it again.

43
00:02:27,915 --> 00:02:31,585
It's an internet cafe
that's open 24 hours.

44
00:02:31,652 --> 00:02:33,654
There is a lot of everything!

45
00:02:33,721 --> 00:02:36,557
They have a drink bar too.

46
00:02:37,825 --> 00:02:39,493
It's cold. I'm done.

47
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,835
Thank you very much.

48
00:02:51,906 --> 00:02:54,208
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

49
00:02:54,909 --> 00:02:56,010
Here you go.

50
00:02:58,245 --> 00:03:01,515
I'm a bit embarrassed
to go to work in this.

51
00:03:01,749 --> 00:03:02,816
Why?

52
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:08,522
I need to wear this at home a couple
of times to get comfortable in it.

53
00:03:08,956 --> 00:03:11,725
I see. Do whatever you like.

54
00:03:11,792 --> 00:03:13,127
Oh, are you upset?

55
00:03:13,827 --> 00:03:14,662
Not at all.

56
00:03:15,996 --> 00:03:16,864
I'm glad.

57
00:03:34,315 --> 00:03:37,618
MACHI SANGENYA
GOOD NIGHT

58
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,989
MACHI SANGENYA

59
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:08,916
Takuma and Hachinohe, you haven't
sold anything this month.

60
00:04:09,316 --> 00:04:10,184
We apologize.

61
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:13,921
Kagimura, you didn't sell
anything this month or any other month.

62
00:04:13,988 --> 00:04:14,989
I know.

63
00:04:15,055 --> 00:04:18,792
Do an open house or something
and sell a house this month.

64
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:23,130
-A condo in Kichijouji, Takuma!
-Yes.

65
00:04:23,530 --> 00:04:25,366
Eifuku town's
single family home, Hachinohe.

66
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:26,567
Yes.

67
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:29,937
Kagimura, you'll take
the single family home in Ochiai.

68
00:04:30,537 --> 00:04:32,873
Mr. Fuse, could you assist
the three of them?

69
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:34,308
What? Assist?

70
00:04:35,042 --> 00:04:37,544
Niwano, what are you doing today?

71
00:04:37,878 --> 00:04:39,980
A 45 year old house in Yotsuya
is done with its renovation,

72
00:04:40,047 --> 00:04:42,116
so I'm going to go take pictures today.

73
00:04:42,416 --> 00:04:45,853
If you could sell that,
that's a major success.

74
00:04:45,919 --> 00:04:48,255
Makabe of Modern Construction
worked hard on the renovation.

75
00:04:48,322 --> 00:04:50,791
It's looking really good.
I'll take pictures, upload them,

76
00:04:50,858 --> 00:04:52,226
and start selling immediately.

77
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,695
-Okay, I'm counting on you.
-Yes, thank you.

78
00:04:54,762 --> 00:04:56,630
-Please sell it for sure.
-I will sell it for sure.

79
00:04:56,964 --> 00:04:59,266
Now, let's all work hard together
as a team!

80
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:01,335
Yes!

81
00:05:02,202 --> 00:05:05,072
Mr. Takuma, Mr. Hachinohe, Kagimura!

82
00:05:05,506 --> 00:05:07,941
Go to your on-site sales
open house now, go!

83
00:05:08,008 --> 00:05:09,343
Yes!

84
00:05:10,277 --> 00:05:11,311
Niwano!

85
00:05:11,612 --> 00:05:12,913
I'm off too!

86
00:05:14,081 --> 00:05:16,116
I'll go meet my client now.

87
00:05:16,417 --> 00:05:18,185
Yes, see you.

88
00:05:18,252 --> 00:05:20,421
CUSTOMER QUESTIONNAIRE.
REIKO BABA

89
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:22,723
I want a house to live in with my mother.

90
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:25,959
Please tell me
your desired location and budget.

91
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:28,529
I don't care about the location.

92
00:05:29,229 --> 00:05:33,500
I have ¥20 million in savings,

93
00:05:34,902 --> 00:05:37,171
and I plan to work until my retirement,
so any house

94
00:05:37,237 --> 00:05:38,605
you think I can afford with that.

95
00:05:39,106 --> 00:05:40,874
How old is your mother?

96
00:05:41,241 --> 00:05:42,676
She's 68 years old.

97
00:05:43,210 --> 00:05:46,914
She raised me all by herself.

98
00:05:47,948 --> 00:05:49,049
I have enough savings,

99
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:51,251
so I can finally do nice things for her.

100
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:52,820
Certainly.

101
00:05:53,253 --> 00:05:57,858
Oh, yes, my mother likes tatami,
please look for a house with tatami.

102
00:05:58,392 --> 00:05:59,293
Please leave it to me!

103
00:05:59,893 --> 00:06:03,597
I will look for a perfect house
for you and your mother.

104
00:06:06,734 --> 00:06:08,569
The white walls
give that spacious feeling.

105
00:06:09,269 --> 00:06:11,271
Mr. Niwano, look at the ceiling too.

106
00:06:11,939 --> 00:06:12,806
That's right.

107
00:06:14,141 --> 00:06:15,743
It's like a studio.

108
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:18,212
I can't believe it.

109
00:06:18,645 --> 00:06:19,546
Before it was renovated,

110
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:21,181
it was an old Japanese style residence.

111
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:26,153
Well, the walls too, but the door
from the entrance to the living room,

112
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:29,490
and the kitchen walls were removed.

113
00:06:30,057 --> 00:06:32,025
So it feels even more spacious.

114
00:06:32,626 --> 00:06:34,928
What's the point of
the bathroom being a see-through design?

115
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:38,599
When that's done,
the living area will seem bigger.

116
00:06:38,966 --> 00:06:42,903
And I wanted to express
that your home is your universe.

117
00:06:44,104 --> 00:06:47,975
An uninterrupted world.
That's my philosophy.

118
00:06:49,076 --> 00:06:50,210
I see…

119
00:06:50,844 --> 00:06:52,846
I've always helped my seniors out.

120
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,849
This is the first home
I did everything as I wanted to.

121
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:57,384
This is your first home?

122
00:06:57,451 --> 00:06:59,620
Yes! I worked hard.

123
00:07:00,187 --> 00:07:02,256
I want anyone who'll live here
to enjoy it too.

124
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:04,391
I'll do my best to sell it.

125
00:07:06,126 --> 00:07:09,963
Ms. Nishihara, you really like that drama.

126
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,132
-I'm back.
-Yes?

127
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:15,903
Ah, it's fine. I'll record it
and watch it.

128
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:17,237
Hey!

129
00:07:17,871 --> 00:07:20,674
Is Manager on the phone
with that person again?

130
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:22,576
It's Ms. Nishihara.

131
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:27,848
He was on the phone when
we got back, so it's been over an hour.

132
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:30,684
Oh, because it's Thursday today.

133
00:07:31,652 --> 00:07:35,422
Ms. Nishihara bought a house
from Manager a long time ago.

134
00:07:36,223 --> 00:07:42,095
The drama on Wednesday nights
has an actor that looks like him,

135
00:07:42,529 --> 00:07:44,998
so she calls him the next day.

136
00:07:46,066 --> 00:07:49,403
Why won't he just hang up? He's an idiot.

137
00:07:49,703 --> 00:07:52,539
-He's too nice, like an idio-
-Be quiet!

138
00:07:54,141 --> 00:07:56,376
Manager has his own plan.

139
00:07:57,211 --> 00:07:58,212
What?

140
00:07:58,679 --> 00:08:01,615
No, I wasn't aware of that at all.

141
00:08:02,449 --> 00:08:04,518
We got married because she got pregnant.

142
00:08:04,852 --> 00:08:07,487
We didn't have time to look for a house.

143
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:11,692
We figured it's a lot to move
after our child is born.

144
00:08:11,758 --> 00:08:14,261
We are newlyweds
and we don't have that much stuff,

145
00:08:14,695 --> 00:08:16,496
and since I'm doing well…

146
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:17,865
How exciting.

147
00:08:18,198 --> 00:08:22,336
You two are both beautiful,
so your baby is sure to be cute.

148
00:08:22,569 --> 00:08:23,437
That's wonderful.

149
00:08:24,571 --> 00:08:29,877
Now, Mr. and Mrs. Aragaki,
I'll swiftly find you a house.

150
00:08:30,310 --> 00:08:31,712
Thank you very much.

151
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:34,348
It's relatively new,

152
00:08:34,615 --> 00:08:36,717
and there are no issues with the building.

153
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:41,188
It's too good to get rid of it.

154
00:08:42,155 --> 00:08:43,390
I want to sell, regardless.

155
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:44,925
I want to sell it fast.

156
00:08:45,459 --> 00:08:47,928
Ms. Sakota, do you have
a desired selling price?

157
00:08:48,762 --> 00:08:49,796
I don't care how much it is.

158
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:55,035
You are not going to ask me
why I'm in such a rush?

159
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:57,638
Is it fine for me to ask you?

160
00:08:59,673 --> 00:09:00,574
I'm getting a divorce!

161
00:09:01,642 --> 00:09:05,078
My husband said it's fine for me
to live in that house,

162
00:09:05,812 --> 00:09:07,714
but it's too big for living alone.

163
00:09:08,248 --> 00:09:11,451
I don't want to live in that house
I shared with that man.

164
00:09:11,752 --> 00:09:15,255
I'm going to sell the house
and take the cash as a divorce settlement.

165
00:09:16,857 --> 00:09:17,724
I understand.

166
00:09:22,195 --> 00:09:23,997
-Oh?
-You pull it.

167
00:09:29,836 --> 00:09:31,872
Thank you for coming today.

168
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:32,973
Please take care of it.

169
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:39,913
Good work. You seem busy.

170
00:09:40,347 --> 00:09:42,115
Mr. Rusudo, you are doing well.

171
00:09:42,649 --> 00:09:44,751
Not at all.

172
00:09:44,818 --> 00:09:46,353
Really?

173
00:09:48,722 --> 00:09:50,691
No matter how well
a couple seems to be doing,

174
00:09:51,325 --> 00:09:54,494
they get a divorce
if something goes wrong.

175
00:09:55,395 --> 00:09:56,496
That client of yours?

176
00:09:57,564 --> 00:10:01,668
For example, a couple
like Ms. Sangenya and Mr. Yashiro will--

177
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:03,670
They won't divorce.

178
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,106
What is your reasoning?

179
00:10:06,373 --> 00:10:08,542
Well, even before they got married,

180
00:10:08,976 --> 00:10:11,545
when they were just boss and subordinate,

181
00:10:11,812 --> 00:10:14,581
Yashiro would always
come here and complain

182
00:10:14,648 --> 00:10:16,583
that Sangenya doesn't listen to him.

183
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:20,587
Even after they got married,
he continues complaining

184
00:10:20,654 --> 00:10:23,123
that she's always home late
and her cooking is a full course meal.

185
00:10:24,057 --> 00:10:27,661
But his complaints are actually
more like bragging about love.

186
00:10:28,028 --> 00:10:29,963
It's the ultimate admission of his love.

187
00:10:30,430 --> 00:10:34,167
It's the form of love beyond that
of couples who are still courting.

188
00:10:35,435 --> 00:10:36,636
I see.

189
00:10:39,373 --> 00:10:40,674
I'm leaving now.

190
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:43,310
Thank you very much.

191
00:10:48,648 --> 00:10:49,883
He opened the door with no issues.

192
00:10:50,684 --> 00:10:52,185
Want some tangerines? I can't eat it all.

193
00:10:52,452 --> 00:10:54,988
Ah, I have a lot of stuff,
so I'll take it tomorrow.

194
00:10:55,055 --> 00:10:56,123
You said that yesterday.

195
00:10:56,189 --> 00:10:58,291
I'll take my stuff home first
then come over.

196
00:10:58,358 --> 00:11:00,594
Ah, I want to use the bathroom too.

197
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,462
-Just come over to my place.
-Oh, okay.

198
00:11:02,729 --> 00:11:03,697
You are right.

199
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,035
OPEN HOUSE

200
00:11:08,101 --> 00:11:10,904
OPEN HOUSE IN PROGRESS

201
00:11:10,971 --> 00:11:14,107
It's far from a station
and there are many slopes.

202
00:11:15,409 --> 00:11:17,244
This is not going to sell.

203
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:20,047
CANTONESE

204
00:11:20,113 --> 00:11:21,481
"It's cold today."

205
00:11:22,616 --> 00:11:24,451
"It's cold today."

206
00:11:24,518 --> 00:11:27,120
Manager Yashiro truly is useless.

207
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:29,122
What? You think so?

208
00:11:29,389 --> 00:11:33,126
When you were the Manager,
it was so much better, Mr. Fuse.

209
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:34,094
OPEN HOUSE IN PROGRESS

210
00:11:34,161 --> 00:11:35,095
Really?

211
00:11:35,495 --> 00:11:37,097
Could I have another one?

212
00:11:37,164 --> 00:11:39,232
-Could I have another one too?
-Yes.

213
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:44,137
Mr. Makabe, what's the most
satisfying moment during work?

214
00:11:45,105 --> 00:11:46,907
Let's see.

215
00:11:47,774 --> 00:11:50,143
For me, I like it the most

216
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:53,780
when I'm putting my flowing ideas
into a design.

217
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:55,482
How about you?

218
00:11:55,749 --> 00:11:57,217
For me, it's when I do the viewing.

219
00:11:57,651 --> 00:12:00,087
I just love it when I see
the excited customers' expressions

220
00:12:00,153 --> 00:12:02,456
when I open the door.

221
00:12:02,923 --> 00:12:04,791
That's totally understandable for me.

222
00:12:04,858 --> 00:12:08,361
Hey, stop with all the "for me".

223
00:12:08,428 --> 00:12:09,830
It's very annoying.

224
00:12:10,464 --> 00:12:11,531
I'm sorry.

225
00:12:11,832 --> 00:12:12,833
Kokoro!

226
00:12:13,366 --> 00:12:14,634
-Welcome.
-Manager.

227
00:12:15,368 --> 00:12:21,074
So my wife would like to learn
how to make your style of yakisoba.

228
00:12:21,141 --> 00:12:23,610
She's shopping for it
right now. Is it okay?

229
00:12:24,010 --> 00:12:26,847
It's fine, but she wants to learn
how to make my yakisoba?

230
00:12:27,114 --> 00:12:33,153
Well, I said I wanted to eat
the soggy yakisoba from Chichin Pui Pui.

231
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:35,822
She insists that she wants
to learn how to make it.

232
00:12:36,189 --> 00:12:37,958
Soggy yakisoba?

233
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:40,160
Hello.

234
00:12:40,227 --> 00:12:41,495
Welcome.

235
00:12:43,830 --> 00:12:45,532
Thank you for helping me.

236
00:12:47,033 --> 00:12:49,503
There, it's like this.

237
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:54,141
Depending on how I feel,
I may or may not add an egg.

238
00:12:54,207 --> 00:12:56,977
Egg is not necessary.
May I try making it now?

239
00:12:57,444 --> 00:12:58,478
Yes, you're going to try?

240
00:12:58,879 --> 00:12:59,713
Yes, I'll try.

241
00:13:25,372 --> 00:13:26,206
It's tasty!

242
00:13:26,473 --> 00:13:27,574
It's not soggy at all.

243
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:30,744
I'm sorry that it's a crispy yakisoba.

244
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:32,279
It really is crispy!

245
00:13:32,579 --> 00:13:35,048
Manager likes soggy yakisoba.

246
00:13:35,115 --> 00:13:37,250
This crispy one is delicious too!

247
00:13:37,517 --> 00:13:38,451
It's delicious!

248
00:13:38,518 --> 00:13:42,355
Show me how to make this
crispy yakisoba. I'll take notes now.

249
00:13:42,422 --> 00:13:46,259
It's easier to make a crispy one.
It's harder to make it soggy.

250
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,563
But I can only make it soggy!

251
00:13:49,629 --> 00:13:51,598
Well, well.

252
00:13:54,601 --> 00:13:55,869
Winner, Adachi.

253
00:13:56,937 --> 00:13:58,205
Winner, Adachi.

254
00:13:59,472 --> 00:14:00,674
Winner, Adachi.

255
00:14:08,014 --> 00:14:08,882
What's the matter?

256
00:14:10,283 --> 00:14:11,918
It's nothing.

257
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:17,791
I'll see you tomorrow.

258
00:14:19,626 --> 00:14:24,397
My clients will buy a house from
your client. What a coincidence.

259
00:14:24,564 --> 00:14:25,398
Yes.

260
00:14:26,766 --> 00:14:28,635
Since my clients are newlyweds,

261
00:14:28,935 --> 00:14:31,605
I won't mention that the previous
homeowner is getting a divorce.

262
00:14:32,439 --> 00:14:33,506
Just in case, you know.

263
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:39,713
The property itself is fine, so it's
not mandatory for me to report it.

264
00:14:42,148 --> 00:14:43,516
A while back,

265
00:14:43,817 --> 00:14:47,053
Sanchi sold a house
where a murder occurred.

266
00:14:47,487 --> 00:14:48,588
I know.

267
00:14:49,155 --> 00:14:51,891
You certainly are a Machi Sangenya expert.

268
00:14:52,259 --> 00:14:53,159
See you.

269
00:15:04,704 --> 00:15:06,706
What a wonderful kitchen.

270
00:15:07,307 --> 00:15:10,143
That island has plenty of storage too.

271
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,114
You are selling such a wonderful house,

272
00:15:14,681 --> 00:15:16,950
but you are moving to a much nicer place?

273
00:15:18,952 --> 00:15:21,755
If you'd like, she will sell you
her furniture as well.

274
00:15:22,022 --> 00:15:24,991
Really? Such fantastic furniture…

275
00:15:26,626 --> 00:15:27,794
What is this?

276
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:29,663
Oh, I hit it with something.

277
00:15:31,531 --> 00:15:33,400
Oh, this part is dented too. See?

278
00:15:34,401 --> 00:15:37,804
The wallpaper is not a big issue
once it's redone.

279
00:15:38,104 --> 00:15:41,608
I'll have it fixed.
Mr. Rusudo, could you arrange it?

280
00:15:41,675 --> 00:15:42,609
Certainly.

281
00:15:43,343 --> 00:15:47,147
It's not the result of you
and your husband arguing?

282
00:15:48,148 --> 00:15:53,420
I heard that relatively new homes
for sale are divorce related.

283
00:15:53,486 --> 00:15:55,255
You are being rude!

284
00:15:55,689 --> 00:15:58,958
We are newlyweds
and we are going to have a child,

285
00:15:59,359 --> 00:16:01,027
so we don't want a house with bad luck.

286
00:16:01,828 --> 00:16:07,701
No, a stepladder hit it
when I was doing washi tape art.

287
00:16:09,903 --> 00:16:10,737
That's fine then.

288
00:16:11,171 --> 00:16:13,707
I think it's a wonderful house,
Mr. and Mrs. Aragaki.

289
00:16:13,773 --> 00:16:15,742
I wonder if we don't apply, it'll sell?

290
00:16:15,809 --> 00:16:18,812
Yes, I think it is better
if you apply now.

291
00:16:18,878 --> 00:16:19,846
Nozomi!

292
00:16:22,349 --> 00:16:23,183
Let's not get a divorce.

293
00:16:24,918 --> 00:16:25,785
Nozomi,

294
00:16:26,853 --> 00:16:28,154
let's not sell this house.

295
00:16:28,822 --> 00:16:30,056
I want to give it a try again.

296
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:31,791
Oh, so it was a divorce?

297
00:16:32,225 --> 00:16:34,027
You didn't have to come home
at a time like this.

298
00:16:34,227 --> 00:16:36,196
The thought of breaking up with you
pains me.

299
00:16:37,263 --> 00:16:39,099
I don't want to be with her anymore.

300
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:44,437
When you started going to the doctor
due to infertility, things got weird.

301
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:46,473
I stopped facing you,

302
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:50,443
and I cheated on you,
but I really want to be with you.

303
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:53,279
I just love you, Nozomi.

304
00:16:53,346 --> 00:16:54,848
It's too late for that!

305
00:16:54,914 --> 00:16:58,585
-Maybe, but I just realized it.
-Let go of me.

306
00:16:59,919 --> 00:17:03,590
I have loved you ever since we were
in elementary school.

307
00:17:03,923 --> 00:17:06,159
My history with you can't be replaced.

308
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:10,463
You are my one and only person.

309
00:17:11,831 --> 00:17:12,766
I realized that.

310
00:17:15,802 --> 00:17:17,070
I understand how you feel.

311
00:17:19,139 --> 00:17:20,440
No matter what happens,

312
00:17:21,141 --> 00:17:25,145
the one and only is your one and only.

313
00:17:26,312 --> 00:17:27,247
Mr. Rusudo?

314
00:17:29,616 --> 00:17:32,185
So you'll break up with that other woman?

315
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,754
I already did.

316
00:17:35,822 --> 00:17:40,693
So does this mean
that you won't sell us this house?

317
00:17:41,761 --> 00:17:43,663
It's fine, Mr. Aragaki.

318
00:17:44,097 --> 00:17:48,401
If this house is not available,
I'll find you another one quickly.

319
00:17:48,468 --> 00:17:49,436
What is going on?

320
00:17:49,702 --> 00:17:50,703
I'm sorry.

321
00:18:00,447 --> 00:18:01,414
What's up!

322
00:18:01,481 --> 00:18:02,515
I'm working right now.

323
00:18:03,817 --> 00:18:08,588
It's far from the station
and the slope to get here is tough.

324
00:18:08,655 --> 00:18:10,390
That's why it won't sell.

325
00:18:11,024 --> 00:18:13,426
Why are you here?
The slopes are really hard.

326
00:18:14,227 --> 00:18:17,931
I just sort of wanted to see you.

327
00:18:20,567 --> 00:18:21,768
How are the kids?

328
00:18:22,101 --> 00:18:23,102
My mom is watching them.

329
00:18:23,369 --> 00:18:25,772
-What about your job at the supermarket?
-I got fired.

330
00:18:27,474 --> 00:18:31,611
That female store manager
was jealous of my beauty! Darn it!

331
00:18:32,011 --> 00:18:34,347
You're the only one
who'd listen to my complaints.

332
00:18:35,515 --> 00:18:36,783
I brought this for you.

333
00:18:37,917 --> 00:18:38,785
What?

334
00:18:40,353 --> 00:18:42,322
You brought ice pop in this cold weather?

335
00:18:42,388 --> 00:18:44,958
-You like ice pop.
-During the summer, I do.

336
00:18:45,024 --> 00:18:47,594
Excuse me. Is this here?

337
00:18:48,261 --> 00:18:50,530
-Yes, it is.
-Welcome.

338
00:18:50,597 --> 00:18:51,998
Can I take a look inside?

339
00:18:52,065 --> 00:18:53,333
Yes, please.

340
00:18:53,399 --> 00:18:55,401
I probably won't buy it,
but I want to take a look.

341
00:18:55,702 --> 00:18:56,736
Let me show you around.

342
00:18:56,803 --> 00:18:58,872
Would you like some ice pop?

343
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:00,206
Please come in.

344
00:19:03,543 --> 00:19:09,616
This is wonderful. If I could see
this view every day, I would be happy.

345
00:19:09,682 --> 00:19:11,451
-I apologize.
-Who is she?

346
00:19:11,751 --> 00:19:13,753
-She's a former employee.
-Your girlfriend?

347
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:15,688
No, that's my ex-wife.

348
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:19,092
That's why you two get along.

349
00:19:19,158 --> 00:19:23,296
Ah, it has a counter in the kitchen.
This is stylish!

350
00:19:23,363 --> 00:19:26,866
A husband and wife should sit
facing the same direction.

351
00:19:27,267 --> 00:19:28,201
I see.

352
00:19:29,002 --> 00:19:30,803
When you face each other, it's not good.

353
00:19:31,104 --> 00:19:32,238
When you see too much,

354
00:19:32,572 --> 00:19:34,274
you will eventually be against each other.

355
00:19:35,275 --> 00:19:39,412
Be quiet. I'll show you to the bedroom.

356
00:19:41,014 --> 00:19:43,583
This is the main bedroom.

357
00:19:43,850 --> 00:19:47,220
It faces east, so you get
plenty of sunshine in the morning.

358
00:19:47,287 --> 00:19:51,457
How wonderful.
If I could've woken up to the sunrise,

359
00:19:51,524 --> 00:19:55,762
I would have loved your silly face too.
Or maybe not!

360
00:19:57,263 --> 00:19:58,565
You are funny.

361
00:19:58,865 --> 00:20:01,801
If he bought me a place like this,
we wouldn't have split.

362
00:20:02,101 --> 00:20:04,671
That's your loss, he seems nice.

363
00:20:05,038 --> 00:20:07,941
But his articulation is bad.

364
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:09,642
Articulation?

365
00:20:10,043 --> 00:20:11,844
I'll show you around the restroom.

366
00:20:12,645 --> 00:20:15,481
I do like this bedroom.

367
00:20:15,848 --> 00:20:16,950
I must say.

368
00:20:18,151 --> 00:20:20,153
But six-five is too expensive.

369
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:23,456
Ah, this could be made into six-three.

370
00:20:23,523 --> 00:20:24,557
Hey!

371
00:20:25,692 --> 00:20:28,995
Why did you two break up?
You're such a perfect match.

372
00:20:30,463 --> 00:20:32,565
I'll consider it, if it's six-three.

373
00:20:32,832 --> 00:20:34,701
Really? That's good news!

374
00:20:34,767 --> 00:20:36,869
Well, sir, six-three is a bit…

375
00:20:36,936 --> 00:20:38,104
Six-three! Six-three!

376
00:20:38,171 --> 00:20:39,505
It's six-three, right?

377
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:40,974
It's six-three, six-three!

378
00:20:41,040 --> 00:20:42,609
-I'll buy it for six-three!
-Thank you!

379
00:20:42,675 --> 00:20:44,544
Don't sell it without my permission!

380
00:20:47,013 --> 00:20:50,283
The charm is that the interior style
is different from the exterior.

381
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:51,951
See-through bathroom?

382
00:20:52,652 --> 00:20:54,187
There's no way. You see it all.

383
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:57,056
The designer said that's the charm.

384
00:20:57,123 --> 00:21:00,460
It's your universe,
your own irregular lifestyle…

385
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:02,962
-This is no good.
-What?

386
00:21:03,029 --> 00:21:04,897
We won't buy it.

387
00:21:05,565 --> 00:21:07,800
Let's go home. This is stupid.

388
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:09,535
Who will live in a house like this?

389
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:11,404
Sir!

390
00:21:16,042 --> 00:21:18,144
This is Makabe, how is it going?

391
00:21:22,081 --> 00:21:24,617
It's my very first work,
so I'm counting on it.

392
00:21:24,684 --> 00:21:27,320
I'll be in Shinjuku later,
so I'll stop by Teiko Real Estate too.

393
00:21:34,861 --> 00:21:36,029
I'm back.

394
00:21:36,095 --> 00:21:37,864
-Welcome back.
-Welcome back.

395
00:21:38,831 --> 00:21:40,099
How did the clients like it?

396
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:42,468
Well, it's not doing well at all.

397
00:21:42,535 --> 00:21:44,904
Even though many people requested a tour…

398
00:21:45,638 --> 00:21:49,308
I'm not sure about that open bath
in this day and age…

399
00:21:49,876 --> 00:21:53,479
I like that open bathroom.
I think it's great.

400
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:55,915
Oh, then why won't you buy it, Tokoshima?

401
00:21:56,282 --> 00:21:58,551
Manager! Isn't this
an act of abuse of authority?

402
00:21:58,618 --> 00:22:00,820
-What?
-Calm down.

403
00:22:00,887 --> 00:22:03,122
I'm heading to the bathroom for now.

404
00:22:03,556 --> 00:22:04,824
Atrocious.

405
00:22:04,891 --> 00:22:07,393
Calm down. Let's all get along.

406
00:22:09,562 --> 00:22:11,197
-I'm back.
-Welcome back.

407
00:22:11,264 --> 00:22:12,265
Welcome back.

408
00:22:14,934 --> 00:22:15,802
Manager.

409
00:22:16,369 --> 00:22:18,871
Yotsuya's renovated property,
I'll sell it.

410
00:22:18,938 --> 00:22:20,006
What?

411
00:22:20,073 --> 00:22:21,774
I've already found a buyer for it.

412
00:22:22,942 --> 00:22:24,644
Who is going to buy it?

413
00:22:24,711 --> 00:22:26,913
-Someone in the neighborhood.
-A neighborhood?

414
00:22:27,847 --> 00:22:28,848
Hello.

415
00:22:29,449 --> 00:22:30,850
I'm Makabe from Modern Construction.

416
00:22:30,917 --> 00:22:32,418
Mr. Makabe! Mr. Makabe!

417
00:22:32,985 --> 00:22:36,923
Chief Sangenya just found a buyer
for that house.

418
00:22:37,156 --> 00:22:38,991
What? Really?

419
00:22:39,358 --> 00:22:42,228
But it'll be renovated
to have tatami mats in all the rooms.

420
00:22:42,862 --> 00:22:43,863
What?

421
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:47,533
It was just redone and you're
going to work on it again?

422
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:48,534
Yes.

423
00:22:50,303 --> 00:22:53,773
If they like a home with tatami,
why not look for another property?

424
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:57,276
It's a waste of money and effort
to renovate again.

425
00:22:57,577 --> 00:23:00,413
That home is Makabe's very first work.

426
00:23:02,415 --> 00:23:04,283
Playing friends won't sell a house.

427
00:23:05,752 --> 00:23:08,321
I'm going to have a meeting
regarding the renovation.

428
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:14,961
Manager! Please stop Chief Sangenya!

429
00:23:15,027 --> 00:23:18,064
I'll look for someone
to buy that home as is!

430
00:23:19,065 --> 00:23:20,166
Mr. Niwano!

431
00:23:24,604 --> 00:23:25,938
Right here.

432
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,307
SHIZUE BABA

433
00:23:28,374 --> 00:23:30,309
Someone in the neighborhood?

434
00:23:32,945 --> 00:23:36,983
It's pretty much the same address
as the renovated home.

435
00:23:39,352 --> 00:23:40,319
Himari-so.

436
00:23:41,687 --> 00:23:42,688
This is it.

437
00:23:43,689 --> 00:23:44,524
SHIZUE BABA

438
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:45,525
This is it.

439
00:23:45,992 --> 00:23:48,161
Will she buy
that property as I renovated it,

440
00:23:48,861 --> 00:23:51,197
without changing it to tatami?

441
00:23:51,731 --> 00:23:53,232
Let's give it a try.

442
00:23:56,502 --> 00:23:57,336
Yes?

443
00:23:59,806 --> 00:24:01,808
What is it?

444
00:24:02,141 --> 00:24:06,445
Sorry to visit so suddenly.
This is my card.

445
00:24:08,414 --> 00:24:09,882
Teiko Real Estate?

446
00:24:10,483 --> 00:24:12,318
Are you Ms. Shizue Baba?

447
00:24:12,819 --> 00:24:13,820
Yes, I am.

448
00:24:13,886 --> 00:24:17,857
Do you perhaps have a plan
to buy a house close by here?

449
00:24:18,191 --> 00:24:20,860
What? A house?

450
00:24:20,927 --> 00:24:21,894
Yes.

451
00:24:22,662 --> 00:24:25,698
I don't have any plans to buy a house.

452
00:24:28,167 --> 00:24:30,536
What's going on? Are you in trouble?

453
00:24:30,603 --> 00:24:33,406
-I don't know.
-Who are you?

454
00:24:33,472 --> 00:24:34,707
They are realtors.

455
00:24:35,241 --> 00:24:37,510
Oh, are they land sharks?

456
00:24:37,577 --> 00:24:39,478
-Are you?
-Not at all!

457
00:24:39,545 --> 00:24:42,415
We won't move out of this place!

458
00:24:42,815 --> 00:24:45,351
-I'm sorry. We made a mistake!
-Wait!

459
00:24:46,018 --> 00:24:48,721
Get it together, Shizu!

460
00:24:48,788 --> 00:24:50,189
Ah, I was shocked.

461
00:24:51,290 --> 00:24:55,695
The other day,
a really flashy realtor woman came.

462
00:24:56,095 --> 00:24:58,865
-I wonder if they are part of that.
-I wonder.

463
00:24:58,931 --> 00:25:02,568
Oh, well! I'm going
to live here until I die!

464
00:25:04,537 --> 00:25:06,939
Let's call Tami and have some tea!

465
00:25:07,006 --> 00:25:08,140
Okay!

466
00:25:10,977 --> 00:25:14,313
Tami! Tami!

467
00:25:15,147 --> 00:25:17,984
-What?
-Tea time!

468
00:25:18,317 --> 00:25:20,052
Okay!

469
00:25:21,287 --> 00:25:23,956
What was this memo for?

470
00:25:27,193 --> 00:25:31,597
I wonder if Ms. Sangenya
is going to put tatami mats in that house.

471
00:25:33,032 --> 00:25:37,370
Mr. Niwano, was my interior design
that bad?

472
00:25:39,805 --> 00:25:42,642
For me, how should I put it?

473
00:25:44,577 --> 00:25:49,482
Now, let's all be positive
and do our best!

474
00:25:50,082 --> 00:25:51,250
-Yes…
-Yes!

475
00:25:51,317 --> 00:25:52,251
Yes!

476
00:25:52,318 --> 00:25:54,220
-Mr. Fuse, please assist Hachinohe.
-Okay.

477
00:25:54,287 --> 00:25:55,454
See you later.

478
00:25:56,022 --> 00:25:58,391
You sold that condo
up on that hill. You have it easy.

479
00:25:58,658 --> 00:26:00,559
Hachinohe! Let's show
Takuma what we can do!

480
00:26:00,626 --> 00:26:01,661
-Yes.
-See you!

481
00:26:02,828 --> 00:26:05,398
Manager, it's Ms. Nishihara on line one.

482
00:26:05,731 --> 00:26:07,633
What? Today's not Thursday.

483
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:09,335
Oh, boy…

484
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:13,839
Good morning, this is Yashiro.

485
00:26:13,906 --> 00:26:16,208
No, it's fine.

486
00:26:16,275 --> 00:26:19,478
I don't want to be like him.
I might just quit.

487
00:26:19,545 --> 00:26:21,013
Why don't you?

488
00:26:21,080 --> 00:26:21,914
Right.

489
00:26:24,350 --> 00:26:27,586
Kagimura, open house,
go to your property! Go!

490
00:26:27,653 --> 00:26:28,554
Yes!

491
00:26:35,161 --> 00:26:36,929
How's it going with the renovated house?

492
00:26:37,496 --> 00:26:41,901
I'm looking for a buyer,
but I can't find one.

493
00:26:42,501 --> 00:26:43,369
I see.

494
00:26:43,703 --> 00:26:45,871
I wonder if that property
has to be the one

495
00:26:46,706 --> 00:26:49,208
for Chief Sangenya's client.

496
00:26:53,446 --> 00:26:56,082
Look, here we go!

497
00:26:58,050 --> 00:27:00,519
It's been a while.

498
00:27:02,722 --> 00:27:04,657
Touch! Touch!

499
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:12,431
Hello, Kenji?

500
00:27:13,399 --> 00:27:16,869
Hachinohe, you are fluent in Chinese,
yet you have to study more?

501
00:27:17,370 --> 00:27:19,472
Oh, no, this is Cantonese.

502
00:27:20,239 --> 00:27:24,310
In Chinese, they have
Cantonese and Mandarin.

503
00:27:24,377 --> 00:27:26,779
In Japan, we say "thank you" in Tokyo,

504
00:27:26,846 --> 00:27:28,481
but in the west, it's different.

505
00:27:29,281 --> 00:27:31,917
That's how different
Cantonese and Mandarin are.

506
00:27:31,984 --> 00:27:34,320
What? That's something.

507
00:27:36,155 --> 00:27:37,289
Welcome.

508
00:27:38,624 --> 00:27:41,827
Hello, I want to take a look
at this house.

509
00:27:42,328 --> 00:27:44,196
This is it. This is Cantonese.

510
00:27:44,997 --> 00:27:46,665
Fine, let's go in then.

511
00:27:49,068 --> 00:27:50,002
How much is it?

512
00:27:50,603 --> 00:27:52,571
-¥90 million.
-That's expensive.

513
00:27:53,005 --> 00:27:54,073
Then that's fine.

514
00:27:54,407 --> 00:27:56,075
There are many others
who will buy this place.

515
00:27:56,575 --> 00:27:59,211
Okay! Okay! I'll buy it!

516
00:28:00,012 --> 00:28:01,113
Thank you.

517
00:28:01,514 --> 00:28:03,616
Let's complete the contract
at the office then.

518
00:28:04,083 --> 00:28:06,719
If you don't hurry,
someone else will buy it.

519
00:28:07,286 --> 00:28:08,921
-Come this way.
-Okay.

520
00:28:08,988 --> 00:28:10,423
What? Did it sell?

521
00:28:11,057 --> 00:28:14,727
Hachinohe! Your personality changes
when you speak Chinese.

522
00:28:21,567 --> 00:28:23,736
I'm sorry to have you come
all the way here.

523
00:28:24,403 --> 00:28:27,573
Don't worry.
I'm sorry about the other day.

524
00:28:29,308 --> 00:28:32,645
Satoshi's clients liked this house too.

525
00:28:36,248 --> 00:28:37,783
It's just my imagination,

526
00:28:37,850 --> 00:28:41,287
but the reason why Mr. and Mrs. Sakota
almost got a divorce…

527
00:28:43,155 --> 00:28:44,824
may be because of this house.

528
00:28:47,359 --> 00:28:51,030
This residential area
is lined with houses of the same design,

529
00:28:51,864 --> 00:28:55,334
and they all have the same
tricycles out front.

530
00:28:57,036 --> 00:29:01,607
You get married,
buy a home, then have a child.

531
00:29:03,142 --> 00:29:04,376
When you see that,

532
00:29:05,478 --> 00:29:08,781
then it's like
any other happiness is not allowed.

533
00:29:09,448 --> 00:29:10,983
Don't you feel that pressure?

534
00:29:11,550 --> 00:29:18,090
I thought maybe the environment
here cornered Mr. and Mrs. Sakota.

535
00:29:19,391 --> 00:29:20,559
Maybe.

536
00:29:22,661 --> 00:29:24,563
Mrs. Sakota is your client, but is it okay

537
00:29:25,998 --> 00:29:27,533
for me to see them now?

538
00:29:32,004 --> 00:29:33,239
Do as you wish.

539
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:38,644
I agreed with Mr. Sakota's words,

540
00:29:39,445 --> 00:29:44,283
and for a moment I forgot my duty
as a realtor to sell a house.

541
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:48,387
I'm a bad realtor.

542
00:29:51,090 --> 00:29:53,025
I won't deal with this case.

543
00:30:04,870 --> 00:30:07,139
I apologize for my sudden visit.

544
00:30:07,206 --> 00:30:12,311
Not at all. Sorry about the mess
the other day.

545
00:30:12,378 --> 00:30:14,547
We decided to give it another try.

546
00:30:14,947 --> 00:30:15,848
Is that so?

547
00:30:16,615 --> 00:30:20,920
We will change the wallpaper
to hide that hole from our fight.

548
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:23,289
We won't sell this house. Sorry.

549
00:30:24,323 --> 00:30:25,758
Please tell Mr. Rusudo that too.

550
00:30:27,326 --> 00:30:29,628
It's great to fix it,

551
00:30:30,663 --> 00:30:33,065
but how about you move to another house?

552
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:38,103
With all due respect,
if you continue to live here,

553
00:30:38,504 --> 00:30:41,106
I feel that your relationship
will deteriorate again.

554
00:30:42,374 --> 00:30:46,445
To change things up and start over,
it's best to change one's home.

555
00:30:49,949 --> 00:30:54,053
Mr. and Mrs. Sakota, this community here

556
00:30:54,420 --> 00:30:57,623
is mainly families with small children,

557
00:30:58,257 --> 00:31:02,595
and I think it's not the best environment
for a husband and wife

558
00:31:02,795 --> 00:31:04,463
with their own jobs and their own world.

559
00:31:06,465 --> 00:31:07,666
You might be right.

560
00:31:10,035 --> 00:31:12,404
Kids' voices in the morning and at night

561
00:31:13,072 --> 00:31:15,207
were actually bothering me.

562
00:31:16,108 --> 00:31:20,045
Living in a house
where neighbors are more private

563
00:31:21,113 --> 00:31:22,648
may suit you better.

564
00:31:25,317 --> 00:31:26,318
You might be right.

565
00:31:28,254 --> 00:31:31,156
You are good.

566
00:31:32,091 --> 00:31:34,460
You are like the missionary of happiness.

567
00:31:34,526 --> 00:31:35,361
Not at all.

568
00:31:37,062 --> 00:31:38,497
I'm just a realtor.

569
00:31:39,632 --> 00:31:41,834
Nozomi, shall we move?

570
00:31:42,868 --> 00:31:43,869
That might be good.

571
00:31:45,170 --> 00:31:48,907
Then I'll search for some properties
and call you tomorrow.

572
00:31:50,542 --> 00:31:51,610
By the way…

573
00:31:54,246 --> 00:31:55,281
Thank you very much.

574
00:31:57,716 --> 00:32:00,452
The other day, I said that
the house of a divorcing couple

575
00:32:00,853 --> 00:32:03,022
is unlucky.

576
00:32:04,990 --> 00:32:07,893
But this is such a wonderful home,
and we couldn't stop thinking about it.

577
00:32:08,327 --> 00:32:10,396
We are grateful too.

578
00:32:16,335 --> 00:32:20,572
Hello, we'll be moving in next door soon.

579
00:32:20,839 --> 00:32:22,574
-We are Aragaki.
-Nice to meet you.

580
00:32:22,808 --> 00:32:24,510
I'm Tomita. Nice to meet you.

581
00:32:24,977 --> 00:32:29,515
Your child and my child
may be in the same grade.

582
00:32:29,882 --> 00:32:32,251
You're right. When is your due date?

583
00:32:32,651 --> 00:32:33,752
Fifth of May.

584
00:32:33,819 --> 00:32:35,087
Mine is the sixth!

585
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:37,856
-Amazing!
-It's so nice to meet you two.

586
00:32:37,923 --> 00:32:39,491
-Likewise.
-Thank you!

587
00:32:42,728 --> 00:32:45,097
I'm going to go sell
that renovated tatami house.

588
00:32:46,865 --> 00:32:48,267
Niwano, is that okay?

589
00:32:51,036 --> 00:32:53,072
-Niwano, you come too.
-What?

590
00:32:53,672 --> 00:32:55,007
-Come!
-Yes!

591
00:32:57,743 --> 00:32:58,577
HIMARI-SO

592
00:32:58,644 --> 00:32:59,712
Yes?

593
00:33:01,413 --> 00:33:02,581
That flashy woman!

594
00:33:02,648 --> 00:33:07,353
I'm Sangenya. Could you come
with me for a moment?

595
00:33:07,853 --> 00:33:08,854
What?

596
00:33:09,588 --> 00:33:10,522
Shizu?

597
00:33:10,589 --> 00:33:12,791
What? What? Are you in trouble?

598
00:33:12,858 --> 00:33:16,195
I don't know what's going on,
but they're trying to take me somewhere.

599
00:33:16,795 --> 00:33:18,230
I won't let you take Shizu!

600
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:21,333
I'll talk with you at a house
two doors down.

601
00:33:21,667 --> 00:33:23,435
If you'd like, please come too.

602
00:33:23,502 --> 00:33:26,405
Your daughter, Ms. Reiko,
is waiting for you there as well.

603
00:33:26,472 --> 00:33:27,873
What? Rei is waiting?

604
00:33:27,940 --> 00:33:30,209
We will continue our talk there.

605
00:33:30,275 --> 00:33:32,344
Ms. Shizue, your friend, go!

606
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:41,954
Thank you for waiting.

607
00:33:42,254 --> 00:33:43,956
I brought your mother.

608
00:33:49,194 --> 00:33:51,163
Mom, I've been expecting you.

609
00:33:52,331 --> 00:33:54,166
I'm going to buy this home,
so let's live together.

610
00:33:54,967 --> 00:33:59,037
I told you many times.
I don't need you to take care of me.

611
00:33:59,738 --> 00:34:02,107
I want to live with you, Mom.

612
00:34:02,474 --> 00:34:06,512
Take care of
yourself and live your own life.

613
00:34:06,812 --> 00:34:09,782
I want to live my life
in the same house with you, Mom.

614
00:34:12,117 --> 00:34:15,621
Ms. Reiko worked hard for 15 years

615
00:34:15,854 --> 00:34:17,923
to buy a home to live with her mother,

616
00:34:18,457 --> 00:34:20,726
who raised her all by herself.

617
00:34:21,627 --> 00:34:23,862
Her dream is about to come true.

618
00:34:24,630 --> 00:34:27,266
Please let Ms. Reiko's dream come true.

619
00:34:27,866 --> 00:34:29,768
Don't bind her with the common notion

620
00:34:30,436 --> 00:34:33,172
that she must devote herself
to her parent.

621
00:34:33,238 --> 00:34:34,406
Then I'll rephrase.

622
00:34:34,907 --> 00:34:38,010
It's the parent's duty
to make the child's dream come true!

623
00:34:40,078 --> 00:34:41,046
Ever since I was a child,

624
00:34:41,780 --> 00:34:46,285
you said that Japanese people
shouldn't lose the tatami culture.

625
00:34:46,952 --> 00:34:49,455
That's why this home is all tatami.

626
00:34:49,855 --> 00:34:53,492
I'm too proud to become a burden to you.

627
00:34:53,926 --> 00:34:55,661
I'm still healthy!

628
00:34:55,727 --> 00:34:57,830
I'm fine going up and down
the stairs at my apartment.

629
00:34:57,896 --> 00:35:01,567
I still hear well,
and I'm quite alert too, right?

630
00:35:01,934 --> 00:35:04,837
-Right! Shizu is amazing!
-Right.

631
00:35:04,903 --> 00:35:09,174
That's why I'm good where I am.
I don't want to go anywhere.

632
00:35:09,241 --> 00:35:12,377
With all due respect, not wanting
to be taken care of by your daughter

633
00:35:12,644 --> 00:35:16,081
isn't the reason why
you're against this idea.

634
00:35:18,484 --> 00:35:20,486
What you are particular about

635
00:35:20,552 --> 00:35:24,990
is not wanting to let go of
your lifestyle at your current residence.

636
00:35:26,492 --> 00:35:30,262
You don't want to let go
of your familiar surroundings

637
00:35:30,329 --> 00:35:31,697
and your friends.

638
00:35:32,831 --> 00:35:38,237
That's why Ms. Sangenya found this
house two doors down from your place.

639
00:35:43,141 --> 00:35:45,077
Tami!

640
00:35:46,478 --> 00:35:48,547
Tami! Tami!

641
00:35:56,522 --> 00:35:58,223
What are you doing here?

642
00:35:58,757 --> 00:36:00,492
It's trouble! Get over here!

643
00:36:01,660 --> 00:36:02,561
Trouble?

644
00:36:03,562 --> 00:36:06,865
You can call her like you did before.

645
00:36:09,301 --> 00:36:13,906
Look, this was
in the mail box this morning.

646
00:36:14,406 --> 00:36:19,444
It's the ad from the Marukan Store.
You don't like those fancy stores.

647
00:36:19,978 --> 00:36:24,249
Trash collection takes burnable trash
on Mondays and Thursdays.

648
00:36:25,083 --> 00:36:28,020
It's the same as where you live now.
Nothing is going to change.

649
00:36:29,922 --> 00:36:30,789
It will change!

650
00:36:31,857 --> 00:36:35,160
Your new life will
have your daughter in it!

651
00:36:39,531 --> 00:36:41,633
I think there's nothing more
you could ask for.

652
00:36:47,005 --> 00:36:50,042
Shizue, what is the problem?

653
00:36:50,108 --> 00:36:53,245
I'm going to be moving in here soon.

654
00:36:53,312 --> 00:36:54,179
What?

655
00:36:56,048 --> 00:36:57,282
I'll live here with my daughter.

656
00:37:02,321 --> 00:37:03,155
But

657
00:37:03,922 --> 00:37:05,958
nothing will change,

658
00:37:06,291 --> 00:37:08,660
so let's go to
Marukan's big sale together!

659
00:37:10,329 --> 00:37:12,264
-Oh, we can go?
-Yes!

660
00:37:12,331 --> 00:37:13,432
I'm glad.

661
00:37:14,232 --> 00:37:16,168
Thank you, Mom.

662
00:37:17,035 --> 00:37:18,270
Isn't it nice?

663
00:37:18,337 --> 00:37:20,072
Thank you, Ms. Sangenya.

664
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:22,507
I've got them.

665
00:37:26,211 --> 00:37:29,381
It's ¥98! We need to go!

666
00:37:29,448 --> 00:37:31,817
You are in the way!

667
00:37:33,685 --> 00:37:35,253
-Niwano!
-Yes.

668
00:37:37,122 --> 00:37:40,258
A house becomes a home
when someone actually lives in it.

669
00:37:40,959 --> 00:37:44,496
The interior design is for the clients

670
00:37:44,730 --> 00:37:46,565
and not for the designer.

671
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:48,166
Yes.

672
00:37:48,233 --> 00:37:52,971
It's important for the elderly
to live in a familiar place.

673
00:37:53,672 --> 00:37:57,009
No matter how extensive
the care and equipment are at a facility,

674
00:37:57,075 --> 00:38:00,145
when they are surrounded
by unknown people at an unknown place,

675
00:38:00,646 --> 00:38:03,181
many elders lose the will to live.

676
00:38:04,082 --> 00:38:05,517
For Ms. Shizue Baba,

677
00:38:05,951 --> 00:38:08,487
this familiar place that she lived in

678
00:38:09,021 --> 00:38:11,790
is one of a kind that can't be replaced.

679
00:38:13,392 --> 00:38:18,563
If you are a realtor,
see what's irreplaceable to your clients!

680
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:20,132
Yes.

681
00:38:20,198 --> 00:38:22,801
If you can't do that,
you won't be able to sell a house.

682
00:38:23,068 --> 00:38:25,937
That's why you can't sell a house!

683
00:38:26,004 --> 00:38:26,838
Yes!

684
00:38:27,806 --> 00:38:30,342
Kagi Channel.

685
00:38:30,842 --> 00:38:31,743
Today we have this.

686
00:38:32,411 --> 00:38:36,581
This is something we give
our clients at Teiko Real Estate.

687
00:38:37,115 --> 00:38:38,517
Sumo-kun--

688
00:38:39,751 --> 00:38:40,719
Hey.

689
00:38:40,786 --> 00:38:45,057
OPEN HOUSE

690
00:38:45,123 --> 00:38:46,992
Do you work for Teiko Real Estate?

691
00:38:47,059 --> 00:38:48,026
Yes.

692
00:38:49,227 --> 00:38:50,729
I saw this ad.

693
00:38:50,796 --> 00:38:53,432
Oh, you are a client? Thank you.

694
00:38:53,965 --> 00:38:56,301
Is there a Manager called Yashiro?

695
00:38:56,702 --> 00:38:57,569
Yes, there is.

696
00:38:58,103 --> 00:38:59,638
So there is.

697
00:38:59,705 --> 00:39:01,206
Do you have something for Manager Yashiro?

698
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:03,542
Yes, I need a favor.

699
00:39:04,509 --> 00:39:06,812
-I'll call him.
-Okay.

700
00:39:11,717 --> 00:39:14,986
He's not answering. I wonder
if he's on the phone again.

701
00:39:18,924 --> 00:39:20,292
Manager!

702
00:39:21,159 --> 00:39:22,828
I just called you!

703
00:39:24,329 --> 00:39:25,230
This is Yashiro.

704
00:39:25,931 --> 00:39:29,301
Did he cause you any trouble, sir?

705
00:39:29,668 --> 00:39:32,804
So you are Manager Yashiro?

706
00:39:33,538 --> 00:39:34,473
Yes, I am.

707
00:39:37,075 --> 00:39:38,110
Well…

708
00:39:38,610 --> 00:39:41,847
Recently, at a family gathering I said
that I was thinking of moving.

709
00:39:41,913 --> 00:39:45,183
Then my dad's cousin's
wife's father's niece

710
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:49,020
told me to talk to Manager Yashiro
from Teiko Real Estate

711
00:39:49,087 --> 00:39:51,123
at Shinjuku office, about real estate.

712
00:39:51,189 --> 00:39:53,091
Your father's cousin's…

713
00:39:53,158 --> 00:39:57,662
Wife's father's niece.
Her name is Mieko Nishihara.

714
00:39:58,730 --> 00:40:00,132
-Oh, Ms. Nishihara.
-Yes.

715
00:40:00,465 --> 00:40:01,600
Nishihara?

716
00:40:02,834 --> 00:40:04,302
That's the long phone call lady.

717
00:40:05,203 --> 00:40:09,107
Ms. Nishihara, you really like that drama.

718
00:40:09,674 --> 00:40:12,978
Ah, it's fine.
I'll record it and watch it.

719
00:40:14,613 --> 00:40:19,184
If you open this up,
it'll be an open living-dining area.

720
00:40:20,619 --> 00:40:24,022
For you, Mr. Minowa,
who value your relatives,

721
00:40:24,656 --> 00:40:27,526
I think this is an ideal house
for a gathering.

722
00:40:28,827 --> 00:40:34,199
The floors have no steps
so it's perfect for small kids

723
00:40:34,733 --> 00:40:36,935
and elderly people
to enjoy their time here.

724
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:41,606
If Mr. Yashiro recommends this place,

725
00:40:41,673 --> 00:40:43,241
then I'll consider it.

726
00:40:44,109 --> 00:40:45,110
Thank you very much.

727
00:40:45,977 --> 00:40:48,280
I'll go home now and bring my wife.

728
00:40:48,647 --> 00:40:50,816
Thank you very much.

729
00:40:52,551 --> 00:40:54,719
So that phone call wasn't a waste.

730
00:40:55,487 --> 00:40:56,521
Kagimura.

731
00:40:58,456 --> 00:40:59,758
I get the job done too.

732
00:41:00,992 --> 00:41:02,794
Manager, you are a manager after all.

733
00:41:03,695 --> 00:41:04,529
CHICHIN PUI PUI

734
00:41:04,596 --> 00:41:07,632
The interior is for the people
who live in it,

735
00:41:08,233 --> 00:41:10,535
and not for the designer.

736
00:41:12,571 --> 00:41:15,207
I'm sorry. Don't feel bad.

737
00:41:16,074 --> 00:41:16,908
No.

738
00:41:18,810 --> 00:41:20,712
Thank you for letting me know.

739
00:41:20,979 --> 00:41:23,982
I will remember Ms. Sangenya's words!

740
00:41:24,749 --> 00:41:26,051
I'm glad.

741
00:41:26,885 --> 00:41:30,722
For me, I was worried
that you would get upset.

742
00:41:30,789 --> 00:41:33,725
For me, I'd like to think
that I'm not that childish.

743
00:41:33,792 --> 00:41:38,496
But for me, I feel that I matured
because of this experience.

744
00:41:39,731 --> 00:41:40,932
Thank you very much.

745
00:41:40,999 --> 00:41:43,168
For me? No need to thank me.

746
00:41:44,836 --> 00:41:47,539
Hey, you said you matured,

747
00:41:47,606 --> 00:41:50,709
but if you don't quit saying "for me"
over and over again

748
00:41:50,775 --> 00:41:52,677
I don't think you could call
yourself a true adult.

749
00:41:52,744 --> 00:41:53,778
Really?

750
00:41:53,845 --> 00:41:55,847
It's annoying!

751
00:41:56,448 --> 00:41:57,315
NIWANO - KAGIMURA - HACHINOHE

752
00:41:57,382 --> 00:41:59,484
Everyone worked hard this month!

753
00:42:00,752 --> 00:42:05,690
Sangenya is a given, but Adachi's sale
is close to hers too.

754
00:42:05,957 --> 00:42:07,893
All the open houses were sold too.

755
00:42:08,193 --> 00:42:09,895
Takuma, Hachinohe,

756
00:42:10,328 --> 00:42:11,997
and Kagimura too. Good job!

757
00:42:13,465 --> 00:42:15,267
What? That's considered as my sale?

758
00:42:15,834 --> 00:42:18,436
Yeah! It's major max!

759
00:42:19,905 --> 00:42:21,673
Major max? What's that?

760
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:25,677
My excitement level is maximum!

761
00:42:28,680 --> 00:42:30,215
-There.
-Thank you.

762
00:42:31,583 --> 00:42:35,487
I haven't heard from Mr. Rusudo
since I left him at that property.

763
00:42:37,355 --> 00:42:39,658
He was acting strange
the last time he was here.

764
00:42:40,292 --> 00:42:41,393
How strange?

765
00:42:41,459 --> 00:42:43,495
He opened the door
like a regular person and left.

766
00:42:44,562 --> 00:42:46,064
That is strange.

767
00:42:47,098 --> 00:42:48,867
MIDORI TOWN FIRST ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

768
00:42:53,772 --> 00:42:55,473
YOSHIO LOVES MANCHICHI

769
00:43:00,211 --> 00:43:02,447
I'm at Midori Town
First Elementary School.

770
00:43:03,148 --> 00:43:05,483
I need to talk to you. Please come.

771
00:43:06,151 --> 00:43:08,119
I'M AT MIDORI TOWN FIRST ELEMENTARY
SCHOOL, I NEED TO TALK TO YOU

772
00:43:19,030 --> 00:43:20,198
I'm at work.

773
00:43:24,936 --> 00:43:25,870
I'll be waiting for you.

774
00:43:30,208 --> 00:43:33,244
You are Yoshio, right?

775
00:43:33,578 --> 00:43:37,549
Manchichi jumped in the pool
and did mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

776
00:43:37,983 --> 00:43:41,686
That mouth-to-mouth
resuscitation tasted like that gyoza.

777
00:43:42,354 --> 00:43:44,622
Ms. Sangenya, it's been fun.

778
00:43:44,689 --> 00:43:45,623
Thank you.

779
00:43:46,057 --> 00:43:48,626
Me too, thank you for your cooperation.

780
00:43:49,394 --> 00:43:51,863
I will pay you back one day.

781
00:43:52,364 --> 00:43:55,233
I would like you to pay me back now.

782
00:44:06,411 --> 00:44:07,545
Manchichi.

783
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:24,829
I've been waiting for you.

784
00:44:27,966 --> 00:44:29,501
I have something to tell you too.

785
00:44:31,236 --> 00:44:33,805
First, let me hear what you want to say.

786
00:44:36,441 --> 00:44:39,544
Well…

787
00:44:40,145 --> 00:44:41,212
Go ahead.

788
00:44:42,781 --> 00:44:44,749
I've reached my limit.

789
00:44:45,150 --> 00:44:46,818
A limit for what?

790
00:44:48,286 --> 00:44:49,220
Well…

791
00:44:50,488 --> 00:44:51,856
Your feelings for me?

792
00:44:55,026 --> 00:44:56,394
-Yes.
-It's an inconvenience.

793
00:44:58,696 --> 00:45:01,833
Whether it's an inconvenience or not,

794
00:45:02,534 --> 00:45:05,737
my body and mind are about to blow up!

795
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:12,177
I became a realtor so that I can

796
00:45:13,044 --> 00:45:14,946
compete with you while selling properties.

797
00:45:18,917 --> 00:45:19,751
But I can't

798
00:45:21,286 --> 00:45:22,153
handle it anymore.

799
00:45:23,922 --> 00:45:27,258
I don't want to observe you from afar.

800
00:45:28,526 --> 00:45:30,128
Manchichi who gave me gyoza,

801
00:45:30,562 --> 00:45:32,630
Manchichi who gave me
mouth-to-mouth resuscitation,

802
00:45:33,131 --> 00:45:34,232
and Manchichi now…

803
00:45:35,033 --> 00:45:36,468
I want all that to be my Manchichi.

804
00:45:38,069 --> 00:45:39,871
You have mistaken me for someone else.

805
00:45:44,109 --> 00:45:47,579
I've never given you gyoza.

806
00:45:49,114 --> 00:45:49,948
Huh?

807
00:45:54,552 --> 00:45:58,189
But you are Manchichi.

808
00:45:58,256 --> 00:46:00,925
Yes, I am Manchichi.

809
00:46:01,693 --> 00:46:03,928
But I didn't give you gyoza.

810
00:46:04,295 --> 00:46:06,764
No, it was Manchichi
who gave me mouth-to-mouth resuscitation

811
00:46:07,132 --> 00:46:10,368
-when I drowned in the pool.
-I didn't.

812
00:46:16,341 --> 00:46:18,376
Manchichi, who's good at magic?

813
00:46:18,743 --> 00:46:19,811
That is me.

814
00:46:22,247 --> 00:46:24,516
Manchichi, who pulls out flags
of all nations?

815
00:46:24,983 --> 00:46:25,917
That is me too.

816
00:46:28,119 --> 00:46:31,456
-Manchichi, who's really popular?
-That's me.

817
00:46:31,923 --> 00:46:33,558
Manchichi, who delivered gyoza?

818
00:46:33,625 --> 00:46:35,593
-That is not me.
-That's a lie!

819
00:46:37,462 --> 00:46:39,964
Manchichi, who gave me
mouth-to-mouth resuscitation…

820
00:46:41,199 --> 00:46:42,934
smelled like gyoza.

821
00:46:44,869 --> 00:46:46,638
-I am right.
-No.

822
00:46:47,539 --> 00:46:52,310
I was watching as you received
mouth-to-mouth resuscitation.

823
00:46:52,810 --> 00:46:55,847
I was watching you
while thinking how ditzy you are.

824
00:46:56,915 --> 00:46:58,583
You drowned and your mind wasn't right.

825
00:46:58,650 --> 00:46:59,951
You misunderstood.

826
00:47:02,787 --> 00:47:05,957
What…

827
00:47:11,129 --> 00:47:15,166
The Gyoza Princess who gave me
mouth-to-mouth resuscitation

828
00:47:16,534 --> 00:47:17,702
became homeless

829
00:47:19,204 --> 00:47:20,538
and said she wanted a home.

830
00:47:21,239 --> 00:47:22,607
That's why I became a realtor.

831
00:47:25,944 --> 00:47:27,412
If that's not the case,

832
00:47:29,581 --> 00:47:30,548
then why…

833
00:47:33,651 --> 00:47:34,586
then why

834
00:47:35,720 --> 00:47:37,522
did I become a realtor?

835
00:47:37,956 --> 00:47:39,023
I don't know.

836
00:47:41,125 --> 00:47:45,230
One thing I can say
is that you really are ditzy.

837
00:47:46,331 --> 00:47:48,433
What? But, but…

838
00:47:49,601 --> 00:47:51,402
When I saw you here last time,

839
00:47:52,370 --> 00:47:54,072
you didn't deny anything.

840
00:47:54,138 --> 00:47:58,443
That's because I didn't understand
what you were talking about.

841
00:48:00,712 --> 00:48:05,950
However, the Gyoza Princess
who secretly delivered gyoza to you,

842
00:48:06,985 --> 00:48:09,387
and the Goddess
who helped you out of the pool

843
00:48:09,454 --> 00:48:11,856
and gave you
mouth-to-mouth resuscitation did exist.

844
00:48:14,125 --> 00:48:15,093
That person is

845
00:48:16,394 --> 00:48:19,130
Kazuko Yamada in the same class.

846
00:48:25,937 --> 00:48:27,505
Kazuko Yamada?

847
00:48:31,943 --> 00:48:32,977
I don't remember her.

848
00:48:33,044 --> 00:48:37,315
It's Kazuko Yamada who sang
at the Midoricho community dance.

849
00:48:38,283 --> 00:48:39,317
I don't know.

850
00:48:39,384 --> 00:48:42,220
Kazuko Yamada. Student number 28.

851
00:48:43,421 --> 00:48:44,355
I don't know.

852
00:48:44,422 --> 00:48:47,925
She was sitting behind you
just before graduation.

853
00:48:48,793 --> 00:48:49,894
I don't remember!

854
00:48:50,128 --> 00:48:54,132
I found Kazuko Yamada!

855
00:48:56,167 --> 00:48:58,403
Please, come in.

856
00:49:10,882 --> 00:49:11,883
Yoshio.

857
00:49:15,086 --> 00:49:17,155
This is your Goddess.

858
00:49:50,355 --> 00:49:51,289
Are you okay?

859
00:49:54,592 --> 00:49:56,027
I'm going home now.

860
00:50:09,741 --> 00:50:10,908
I won't forgive her.

861
00:50:15,947 --> 00:50:17,715
Machi Sangenya.

862
00:50:20,151 --> 00:50:21,285
I will not forgive her.

863
00:50:26,157 --> 00:50:28,259
There is no property I can't sell.

864
00:50:28,326 --> 00:50:29,660
I won't give away Shinjuku.

865
00:50:29,727 --> 00:50:32,663
A.I. Machi Sangenya
will destroy Machi Sangenya.

866
00:50:32,730 --> 00:50:35,366
Do you, the genius realtor,
have something to say to me?

867
00:50:35,433 --> 00:50:36,334
¥10 billion!

868
00:50:36,401 --> 00:50:38,102
Buy all the rooms.

869
00:50:38,169 --> 00:50:41,105
There is no property I can't sell!
